Operational and Financial Reporting
element.documentation: The service reports on operational and financial business indicators, such as: - financial statement on contingencies - amount of power managed - etc.

element.name: Observe Grid Safety Threat
element.documentation: This event represents a generic potential security threat in the grid configuration that has a possible effect on the state.

element.name: Incident & Problem Handling
element.documentation:
This process responds to unforeseen disruptions, allowing us to minimize the impact on the operated capacity management process to keep the grid secure and safe by fulfilling D/R products. It also captures incidents in the supporting IT infrastructure.
The grid incidents are visualized and processed by different people, and the following state are defined:
Normal state (TSO): - ‘normal state’ means a situation in which the system is within operational security limits in the N-situation and after the occurrence of any contingency from the contingency list, taking into account the effect of the available remedial actions. - Operational limits are NOT violated.
Emergency state (TSO): emergency state’ means the system state in which one or more operational security limits are violated. - Operational limits are violated, requires immediate corrective actions.
Alert state (TSO) ‘alert state’ means the system state in which the system is within operational security limits, but a contingency from the contingency list has been detected and in case of its occurrence the available remedial actions are not sufficient to keep the normal state.

element.name: Notify Grid State Change
element.documentation: The event represents a detected safety threat with a possible effect on the state of the grid and the start of a safety assessment to determine the risk level.

element.name: Manage Operational Security Limits
element.documentation: Business Process that handles creation, update, validation, and provisioning of operational security limits for equipments, equipment containers and point or areas in the grid.

element.name: Perform Risk & Safety Assessment
element.documentation:
The 'perform risk & safety assessment’ process executes serveral security analysis to establish an electrotechnical state of an area or point in the grid as defined by a contingency. It usages the operational limits, so that, based on a risk profile, the problem can be quantified.
- retrieve operational limits (from grid contingency registry) -> operational limit policy manager - evaluate forecasted measurements, calculated state-variables to the defined operational limits - validate grid quality (perform a state-estimation) - calculate and fill in missing states on equipments/measurements - retrieve action controls from OCR to adjust the predicted capacity on parts of the grid

element.name: Supervise & Reporting Contingencies
element.documentation:
This process registers a grid configuration with a contingency. Adding a new contingency, updating the choreography for a contingency, and supervising the contingency are sub-processes.
A Contingency indicates a situation that may threaten the safety and/or balance of the electricity grid and currently represents a record of an issued “conditional” transport restriction. This process registers the corresponding grid configuration and supervises the 'operate capacity management' process for the included sub-processes based on choreography structure.

element.name: Operate Capacity Management
element.documentation: The process 'Operate Capacity Management’ (=OCM) provides by continuously running a grid security analysis, and performing a safety & risk assessment in our system with a match of demand/response products to ensure a secure & balanced grid.

element.name: Request Contingency Analysis
element.documentation: The event represents a scheduled request from supervising the contingencies.

element.name: Operational Management & Reporting
element.documentation:
The goal of this process is to provide various reports about operations. An example of such a report is a compliance report, i.e., a report to justify that in a certain time frame Alliander complied with its contractually agreed on behavior. Similarly, reports to justify that a client did/did not comply with its contractually agreed on behavior. Financial reporting is a sub-process. Based on control actions, what were the financial consequences? Were they within the pre-programmed budgetary agreements for a given congestion area? Besides compliance and financial reporting as stated above, the process also administers the operating limits and policies. Think of dynamic operating limits. As a consequence of dynamic limits the operating constraints per (client) contract may have to be re-evaluated.
The process 'Operational Management & Reporting' provides reports on the financial and operational performance business indicators. It register the financial impact on remedial actions on the different products. The operational limits sets on equipment's are provided and used to determine the risk for a grid configuration.

element.name: Observe Grid State Change
element.documentation: This event represents a generic change in de configuration of the grid that has an effect on the state, like a switch change, update of asset limit, etc.

element.name: Cost Center
element.documentation: For each contingency a cost-center is registered for accumulate financial expenses/revenues to report on.

element.name: Control Action Report
element.documentation: The action control represents the expected capacity behaviour defined by the operatin and financial constraints as part of a Settlement. The operating contraint is exchange as a schedule with the Market Participant on a defined RegisteredIntertie. This operating constraint is then related to the EnergyConsumer as ControlAction to make this connectively available for grid-calculations.

element.name: Virtual Grid Snapshot
element.documentation: A virtual grid snapshot is not an concrete business object, but it represents a part of the grid in a defined state (operational, energized) to perform a hypothesis.

element.name: Scenario Analysis
element.documentation: A scenario defines the operating parameters, when executing a study on a contingency.

element.name: Safety Assessment
element.documentation:
A safety assessment is a result of a performed risk assessment and represents the 'system state' of an analysed part of the grid.
This includes: - the topological island with related equipments, - the connectivity between these equipments, - the exceedense of the operational limits , - the identified contingency equipments (the one causing the transport limitations) - the allocated operating constrains exchanged with the market-participants
The 'system state' gives direction in the possibility of reaching a solution. Here, the action perspective plays a role and thus also determines the serverity level.

element.name: Contingency Study
element.documentation:
A study is a set of analysis and/or solutions with a common purpose performed as part of a single business process.
The study defines the unit-of-work.

element.name: Remedial Action Evaluation Report
element.documentation:
The Evalution Action Report is the result of a verificatio process to determine whether a market participant has complied with settlement conditions, such as operating and financial constraints.
-> proposal to rename this: remedial action evaluation report

element.name: Contingency
element.documentation:
A Contingency indicates a situation that may threaten the safety and/or balance of the electricity grid, and represents a record of an issued “conditional” transport restriction.
This includes the following definitions: - Contingency - The identified and possible or already occurred fault of an element, including not only the transmission system elements, but also significant grid users and distribution network elements if relevant for the transmission system operational security (source: EU regulations 2019/943). - The object "Contingency" is defined: "An event threatening system reliability, consisting of one or more contingency elements." (source: IEC 61970 UML version ‘IEC61970CIM17v40’, dated ‘2020-08-24’.) - A contingency is the identified and possible or already occurred fault of an element, including not only the transmission system elements, but also significant grid users and distribution network elements if relevant for the transmission system operational security. (reference: CONTINGENCY PROFILE SPECIFICATION - entso-e)
The contingencies are used for - define the part of the grid to perform a security analysis by executing a study - administer the related financial impact of remedial actions - administer the related operational impact of remedial actions

element.name: Incident
element.documentation: An Incident is defined as a planned or unplanned interruption or reduction in quality of an service that has the potential to result in a breach or degradation of system state of the grid.

element.name: Risk Evaluation Policies
element.documentation:
To determine the risk level and corresponding 'energy system state', like alert state or emergency state policies applied. The specified policies are related to the different equipments and other parts of the grid.
risk = impact * change
drivers for risk determination: - VBM (CAIDI - calculated average interuption duration index) - potential power lost (not relevant for TenneT process integration) - unreliable frequency containment reserve ( due to contingencies in DSO grid) - Low Frequency Demand Disconnect (LFDD) not in an effective state

element.name: Product Assignment Policies
element.documentation: The represents policies for mix and match of products within tolopological island. For compliancy requirements, the policies applied are traceable over time.

element.name: Capacity Settlement Dossier
element.documentation:
A capacity settlement dossier is the result of cary-out a solution fulfillment for capacity management.
Naming of Settlement is taken from: REDISPATCH & COUNTERTRADE COST SHARING IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE https://eepublicdownloads.entsoe.eu/clean-documents/CIM_documents/Grid_Model_CIM/RD_CT_Cost_Sharing_IG_v1.0.pdf

element.name: Registered Resource
element.documentation: The Registered Resource represents the operational conditions of the D/R product as operated by the Market Participant in order to change the potential behaviour on the point of common coupling (usage point) .

element.name: Settlement Condition
element.documentation:
In the context of electricity markets and Demand Response (D/R) products, settlement conditions refer to the rules, processes, and criteria for calculating payments, penalties, and performance evaluations for participants who provide demand-side flexibility.
The settlement conditions describe the amount of capacity that needs to be managed (mitigate, curtailled, etc) these conditions are communicated to agents (IT-components), to search for a possible solution based on a particular D/R product.

element.name: Create Grid State Insight
element.documentation: The 'grid state insight' process creates a representation of the grid, that includes all electrotechnical components, measurements (based on sensor meter readings, forecasts, switching states). It also describes connected participants, represented as leafs in the grid to with draw or inject energy in the grid. This representation also includes the relation to the point (MarketEvaluationPoints) for allocation and reconsolidation.

element.name: Perform Risk & Safety Assessment
element.documentation:
The 'perform risk & safety assessment’ process executes serveral security analysis to establish an electrotechnical state of an area or point in the grid as defined by a contingency. It usages the operational limits, so that, based on a risk profile, the problem can be quantified.
- retrieve operational limits (from grid contingency registry) -> operational limit policy manager - evaluate forecasted measurements, calculated state-variables to the defined operational limits - validate grid quality (perform a state-estimation) - calculate and fill in missing states on equipments/measurements - retrieve action controls from OCR to adjust the predicted capacity on parts of the grid

element.name: Execute & Verify Solution Fulfillment
element.documentation:
The 'Execute & Verify Solution Fulfillment' provides the analysis of the defined capacity situation, where there is sufficiency or insufficiency amount of transport capacity available is. The process performs a mix&match of available capacity products, such as early curtailment, redispatch, late curtailment or flexibility, on the different time-lines, such as day-ahead, intra-day and realtime.
In executing the fulfillment each capacity product has its own sub-process to carry out to settlements, this includes selection, offering, confirm and activate a settlement. The settlement includes operating and financial constraints on which the market participant need to comply.
In executing the fulfillment of the situation on the grid is guareded by a capacity settlement dossier and contains the progress state of the different settlement options. These options are offered by the connected and selected agents.
When a settlement is activated, there is a verification of the market participants complies with the agreed constraints, such as operating and financial.
The process finished, when the solution fulfillment performs all actions to solve the defined capacity situation or/and the residual risk is accepted.

element.name: Prepare Contingency Security Analysis
element.documentation:
This provides the steps to prepare the information and determine the conditions/contexts to perform several individual security analysis.
This process contains : - retrieving required information and validating whether the follow-up process is ready to be carried out. - determining, based on questions, which security analyses should be performed and with what granularity. - retrieving the configuration configuration (or general policy), as it should be monitored. - check and validate the completeness of the information
-> ophalen van benodigde informatie en valideren of het vervolgproces instaat om uitgevoerd te worden. -> het bepalen op basis van vraagstellingen, welke security analyses uitgevoerd dienen te worden en met welke granualiteit. -> ophalen van de configuratie van de configuratie (of algemene beleid), zoals deze bewaakt dient te worden.
-> volledigheidscontrole
It consists of: - retrieve - evaluate forecasted measurements, calculated state-variables to the defined operational limits - calculate and fill in missing states on equipments/measurements - retrieve action controls from OCR to adjust the predicted capacity on parts of the grid

element.name: Performing Risk Assessment
element.documentation:
This is the proces to identifiying and measuring risk based on the different security analysis.
An simple risk assessment is performeed on one aspect: - capacity overloads (active-power, reactive-power, apparent-power, current) - voltage overloads

element.name: Perform Security Analysis
element.documentation:
The security analysis is a simulation that check violations on a network. These checks can be done on the base case or after a contingency, with or without remedial actions.
The security analysis will be performed on all equipments, an equipment is flagged as contingencyEquipment when it violates the operational limits.
When capacity products are active in this topological Island, these (MV-route), ControlActions are not part of the realtime contingency analysis, because these represents a futer state.
Only an analysis on: - active-power, reactive-power, apparent-power - voltage - current
This process contains: -> the execution of the analysis and the observation whether have gone inside/outside the operational security limits. -> compacting the analysis and it results in only the exessaen. -> validate grid quality (performed by a state-estimation calculation) -> matching the operational limits to the calculated values within the topological island -> assign the equipments with a potential overrun on the operational limits.

element.name: Create Topological Projection
element.documentation: An topology analysis is performed by a topology processor and contains basicly of two steps: firstly, combine the connectivity node to form the topological node; and secondly, partition the network to form topological island.

element.name: Automated and Activate Settlements
element.documentation: This process identifies the different options that can contribute to solve a capacity request in cooperation with the available agents, re-evaluates the base safety assessment.

element.name: Perform Compliancy Verification
element.documentation:
A verification takes operating constrains, which are exchanged with the market participant and compares these with the actual measuremens in a defined time-frame. Based on this verification its detemined wherther the market participant has followed these constraints.
This process only verifies and doesn't take action when market participant doesn't comply with the settelement.

element.name: Carry Out Product-Specific Solution Fulfillment
element.documentation:
When executing multiple types of D/R product it has its own characteristics in operating these products. These products are offered to different marktet participants with each its own platforms or standards.
This process carries-out specialize in handling these D/R products for different time frame, like day-ahead, intra-day, real-time, etc.

element.name: Contingency Management Service
element.documentation: Provides functionalities to view, filter, search, and sort all physical entities in the grid that are measurable ("contingencies"). It also offers detailed views of these contingencies, including associated scenarios, equipment, customers, and market product configurations.

element.name: Contingency Record Service
element.documentation: Provides functionalities to view, filter, search, and sort all physical entities in the grid that are measurable ("contingencies"). It also offers detailed views of these contingencies, including associated scenarios, equipment, customers, and market product configurations.

element.name: Data Monitoring & Analysis
element.documentation: This involves gathering and displaying real-time and forecasted data related to power flow, congestion, and grid parameters.

element.name: Charting and Visualization Service
element.documentation: Offers various graph types to visualize measured values, forecasts, and congestion limits over specified time periods and intervals.

element.name: Archive & Log Service
element.documentation: Enables access to historical data, including past congestion cases (Case Archive), records of contract violations, and a log of business exceptions and missing measurements.

element.name: Operational and Financial Reporting
element.documentation: The service reports on operational and financial business indicators, such as: - financial statement on contingencies - amount of power managed - etc.

element.name: Fulfill Demand/Response Products Service
element.documentation: The 'Fulfill Demand/Response Product Service' provides fulfillment for a defined capacity situation, and mix and match different D/R products, such as early curtailment, redispatch, late curtailment or flexibility, on the different time-lines, such as day-ahead, intra-day and realtime.

element.name: Energy Inject & With-drawn Prediction Service
element.documentation: The 'Energy Inject & With-drawn Prediction Service' predicts the injection and with-drawn of energy in an area or point in the grid based on multi conditions, like wheater, etc. A prediction is based on meter readings or predefined profiles.

element.name: Guarantee energy system security
element.documentation:
"Guarantee Energy System Security" refers to the measures and strategies implemented to ensure the reliability, stability, and resilience of an energy system. This involves protecting energy infrastructure from disruptions, maintaining a balance between supply and demand, and ensuring uninterrupted access to energy resources. Key aspects include:
- Grid Reliability: Ensuring stable electricity generation, transmission, and distribution to prevent blackouts or failures. - Energy Supply Diversification: Utilizing multiple energy sources (renewables, fossil fuels, nuclear) to reduce dependency on a single supply chain. - Regulatory and Policy Frameworks: Implementing government policies and market mechanisms to promote energy security and sustainability.

element.name: Operational Capacity Allocation Service
element.documentation:
This service supports the 'control of active/reactive power' on parts of the grid, to optimize the loading of equipment so problems can mitigated and secure the overall integrity of the grid.
This can be performed by predefined schedules defined by the system operator or base on prior requested capacity by an flexibility service provider that is granted and then allocated for operation.

element.name: Energized Grid Topology Service
element.documentation: The 'Energized Grid Topology Service' provides an energized topology, including the functional electrotechnical components, their mutual relationships and measurements, the postion of the different active demand/response products based on a specific use case.

element.name: System Risk State Assessment Service
element.documentation: The 'System Risk State Assessment Service' determines the energy risk state for an area or point in the grid, based on a timestamped topology, including prediction (forecasted/estimated - load&generation and compared those to the grid & system limits.

element.name: Capaciteit Inpassing Indicatie Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit om vast te stellen of de capaciteit behoefte van (potentiële) klant informeel gehonoreerd kan worden. Met het doel om een match te kunnen maken tussen de klant capaciteitbehoefte en de beschikbare capaciteit met een snelle en efficiënte indicatie zonder een directe match te maken tussen de beschikbare demand- en response producten in het transport-producten-portfolio.

element.name: Klant Capaciteit Behoefte Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor het administreren van klantbehoeftes voor een compleet begrip over het operating model van de klant, zijn vrijheidsgraden in operatie, vrijheid in locatie en geplande implementatietijd. Het doel is het vormen van een totaal klantbeeld rondom zijn transportcapaciteit behoeftes.

element.name: Demand/Response Product Catalogus Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor inzicht in de alle Demand en Response producten beschikbaar en gepland met hun interne- en externe beschrijvingen en eigenschappen. Het doel is om op een uniforme en actuele manier de informatie te kunnen voorzien aan klanten en interne medewerkers vanaf minimaal de oriëntatiefase van klanten.

element.name: Inpassing Risico Afweging Service
element.documentation: >ideation Deze service ondersteund het afwegen van de risico’s voor inpassing van een klant capaciteitsbehoefte en registreert de afwegingen en gemaakte keuze.

element.name: Klant Aanvraag Support Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor de opvolging en bewaking van verschillende taken/activiteiten, die het gevolg zijn van een klant capaciteitsaanvraag met als doel inzicht te bieden in de voortgang en maatregelen te kunnen nemen bij o.a. vertragingen.

element.name: Klant Betaalhistorie Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor inzicht in alle financiële transacties tussen de DSO en de klant met belangrijke eigenschappen zoals: overschrijding van betalingstermijnen, etc. Het doel is om de betrouwbaarheid van de klant vast te stellen tijdens het maken van afspraken (b.v. contracteren, oplossen van problemen). Inclusief waarborging van de data privacy.

element.name: Transport Verwachting Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor inzicht op een uniforme manier over de verwachtte (levering/opname) van toekomstige transportcapaciteit van een functioneel elektrotechnisch component inclusief overdrachtspunten. Het doel is om in staat te zijn de behoeftevraag te beoordelen en benodigde netverzwaring te kunnen identificeren.

element.name: Kosten Indicatie service
element.documentation:
>ideation Deze service biedt een indicatie van de klantkosten bij een aanbod of selectie van Demand- response producten inclusief een firm-transport met het doel dat op een effectieve en efficiënte wijze de klant zijn beste aanbieding kan vinden.
-> is kosten wel een goede term, dit is de prijs voor de klant. (hij doet de uitgafe en maakt daarbij kosten)

element.name: Capaciteit Inpassing Service
element.documentation: >ideation Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor inzicht in de beschikbare netcapaciteit over een langere termijn op basis van een formele doorrekening met een simulatie van de klantinpassing inclusief alle te adviseren demand/response producten. Het resultaat is de operationele restrisico’s zoals overschrijding capaciteit, kortsluitvastheid, spanningshuishouding, en eventueel overige. Het doel is op een verantwoorden en efficiënte manier formele afspraken te maken met een klant zoals een adviesaanbod of offerte.

element.name: Capaciteit Orientatie Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt iedereen in het Liander verzorgingsgebied de mogelijkheid om zich te oriënteren op een passende capaciteit oplossing gebaseerd op de lokale netsituatie, Liander productaanbod, technische mogelijkheden en specifieke klantbehoefte.

element.name: Klant Administratie Service
element.documentation:
Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor het aanbieden en administreren van basis klantdata en verzorgt de relatie met overige klantdata (obv klantinteractie zoals klant contact) inclusief waarborging van de data privacy.
2025-04-15 Adminstrating and Managing Customer Service

element.name: Klant Contact Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor klantcontact welke compliant is met integrale klantbediening. Het doel is om alle interactie te waarborgen waarmee bij elk klantcontact de laatste real-time bekende status wordt meegenomen door elke medewerker in het bedrijf, ongeacht het communicatiekanaal. Inclusief waarborging van de data privacy

element.name: Capaciteit Aanvraag Service
element.documentation:
Deze service biedt de klant de mogelijkheid om de capaciteitsbehoefte formeel in te dienen bij Alliander. Optioneel met de gekozen passende oplossing vanuit de eerdere oriëntatie.
-> zou dit dan niet Klant Capaciteits Aanvraag Service moeten zijn.

element.name: Oriëntatie Netcapaciteit Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor inzicht in de beschikbare netcapaciteit over een langere termijn op basis van gereduceerde effort met het doel om de gebruiker te laten oriënteren in de beschikbare capaciteit in het net van Liander over een tijdsperiode.

element.name: Capaciteit Inpassing Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt specifiek, voor klanten gegenereerde of berekende data voor nieuwe of veranderende transportbehoeftes. Het uiteindelijke doel is om de meest passende transportvraag voor de klant te kunnen offreren. Dit wordt bereikt door te bevestigen dat het operationele risico van het aan te bieden transport (met demand- response producten) geaccepteerd kan worden.

element.name: Transport Historie Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt functionaliteit voor inzicht in het historisch transport (levering/opname) op een geaggregeerd niveau van de klant, ongeacht zijn overdrachtspunt, met de doelen om de beschikbare netcapaciteit te bepalen in een stationaire situatie (b.v. de klant verzoekt geen wijzigingen, er is geen groei verwacht) en om de klant beter te begeleiden tijden zijn oriëntatie en adviesfase.

element.name: Capaciteit Oriëntatie Advies Service
element.documentation: Deze service biedt de klant extra advisering in geval de Capaciteit Oriëntatie Service niet volstaat. Advisering kan zowel online via AI chat-bot dan wel via persoonlijk contact met Alliander of extern energie adviseur.

element.name: Switching Order Supervision
element.documentation: Trigger: A switching order is issued (e.g., for maintenance, fault isolation, or grid reconfiguration).

element.name: Calculate and Publish TenneT pocket limits
element.documentation: Responsible for correct height of current exchange limits (together with TenneT) and keeping up to date the Excel file on Sharepoint where all exchange limits are stored internally.

element.name: Real-Time Data Collection Process
element.documentation: Initiates and manages the continuous acquisition of data from SCADA systems, sensors, and external sources.

element.name: Operate Grid Management
element.documentation:
The process 'Operate Gird Management’ (=OCM) is a core business capability within electric utility operations, responsible for the real-time control, monitoring, and optimization of the electrical distribution grid. It ensures the safe, reliable, and efficient delivery of electricity to consumers while maintaining grid stability and complying with regulatory and operational standards.
- Maintain grid stability under normal and emergency conditions - Ensure safe operation of assets and personnel - Enable coordination with Transmission System Operators (TSOs) and other stakeholders - Support automated and manual control of grid elements

element.name: Enable Maintenance of the Grid
element.documentation:
Enable Maintenance of the Grid
Business Service: Grid Maintenance Coordination
Processes: Schedule planned maintenance Notify stakeholders (DSOs, TSOs, customers) Isolate grid sections for safe work Monitor maintenance execution and completion

element.name: Safe-Guarding the Installed Assets
element.documentation: Safe-Guarding the Installed Assets Business Service: Asset Protection and Monitoring Processes: Real-time asset condition monitoring Intrusion detection and alarms Environmental hazard monitoring (e.g., flooding, fire) Preventive maintenance planning

element.name: Restoration of the Grid
element.documentation: Restoration of the Grid Business Service: Grid Restoration Management Processes: Fault detection and isolation Prioritize restoration zones Re-energize grid sections Communicate with emergency services and stakeholders

element.name: Perform All Kinds of Switching Procedures
element.documentation: Perform All Kinds of Switching Procedures Business Service: Switching Operations Management Processes: Validate switching requests Execute remote/local switching Log switching events Confirm system stability post-switching

element.name: Perform All Kinds of Tap-Changer Procedures
element.documentation: Perform All Kinds of Tap-Changer Procedures Business Service: Voltage Regulation Management Processes: Monitor voltage levels Execute tap-changer adjustments (manual/automatic) Coordinate with SCADA systems Record tap positions and impacts

element.name: Perform Remedial Action on Instructions of the TSO on All Limitation Drivers
element.documentation: Perform Remedial Action on Instructions of the TSO on All Limitation Drivers Business Service: TSO Coordination and Remedial Action Execution Processes: Receive and validate TSO instructions Execute load shedding, reconfiguration, or redispatch Monitor system response Report back to TSO

element.name: Grid Contingency Manager (GCM)
element.documentation: grid contingency manager (GCM):- an application service to administrate and manage the contingencies specifying the grid area to operate capacity management.

element.name: Grid Meister
element.documentation: record cases for congestion management

element.name: Activated Settlement Analyzer (ASA)
element.documentation: activated settlement analyzer (ASA) :- an application service to determine and publish the impact of activated settlements (including the operating constraints) on different types of equipment in the grid.

element.name: Registered Resource Manager (RRM)
element.documentation: prior MAS

element.documentation: dynamic saftey assessor (DSA) :- an application service to process to analyse a grid state of a topological island at a moment in time and to determine the energy grid state.

item.documentation: The ability to develop and manage goods and services strategy and plans.

item.documentation: The ability to determine a strategy that realizes mission and vision through strategic goals.

item.label: C.1.2 Acquire and manage customer agreements
item.documentation: The ability to enter into and manage agreements with customers.

item.documentation: The ability to exchange data with energy market parties, completely and at the right time, to guarantee market functionality.

item.label: C.6.1 Serve market parties and maintain relations
item.documentation: The ability to serve energy market parties, so that they can participate in the market processes, and maintain relations between them.

item.label: C.6.3 Perform/facilitate market processes
item.documentation: The ability to perform/facilitate market processes.

item.label: C.6.2 Manage market data

In ArchiMate, if you want to model a business function that proxies or intermediates another function like data collection or acquisition from systems, you're essentially dealing with a delegation, abstraction, or orchestration role. The key is to express that this function does not perform the work itself but facilitates, routes, or acts on behalf of others. Suitable ArchiMate Business Function Names
Here are some fitting business function names for a proxy-style function that collects or acquires data indirectly: 1. Data Mediation
Rationale: Reflects an intermediary role that translates, routes, or proxies data flows.
Usage: Common when integrating heterogeneous systems or acting as a broker.
2. Data Brokerage
Rationale: Implies indirect access to data; the function "brokers" or intermediates access.
Usage: Useful in data marketplaces or where access control, governance, or abstraction is involved.
3. Data Aggregation
Rationale: Abstracts and collects data from multiple sources.
Usage: Suitable when the proxy function combines or summarizes data rather than just relaying it.
4. Data Acquisition Coordination
Rationale: Coordinates actual data collection, without directly implementing it.
Usage: Implies management/coordination responsibilities.
5. Data Access Provisioning
Rationale: Highlights the role of controlling or enabling data access from systems.
Usage: Common in API gateway or data service management contexts.
6. Data Retrieval Orchestration
Rationale: Orchestrates the retrieval without necessarily retrieving itself.
Usage: Relevant in SOA/Microservice landscapes.
Modeling Approach
You can model the proxy business function as having a realization relationship from a business service like Data Access Service.
The actual data collection can be modeled as a sub-function or a separate function realized by another component or actor.
Use assignment or serving relationships to show how the proxy is used by a business role (e.g., Data Analyst, System Integrator).

This process register a grid configuration with an contingency. Adding a new contingency, updating the choreography for a contingency and supervising the contingency are sub-processes.
A Contingency indicates a situation that may threaten the safety and/or balance of the electricity grid, and represents a record of an issued “conditional” transport restriction. This process register a grid configuration with an contingency and supervise the 'operate capacity management' process for the included sub-processes based on choreography structure.

The grid incidents are visualized and processed by different people, and the following state are defined:
Normal state (TSO): - ‘normal state’ means a situation in which the system is within operational security limits in the N-situation and after the occurrence of any contingency from the contingency list, taking into account the effect of the available remedial actions. - Operational limits are NOT violated.
Emergency state (TSO): emergency state’ means the system state in which one or more operational security limits are violated. - Operational limits are violated, requires immediate corrective actions.
Alert state (TSO) ‘alert state’ means the system state in which the system is within operational security limits, but a contingency from the contingency list has been detected and in case of its occurrence the available remedial actions are not sufficient to keep the normal state.

The 'perform risk & safety assessment’ process executes serveral security analysis to establish an electrotechnical state of an area or point in the grid as defined by a contingency. It usages the operational limits, so that, based on a risk profile, the problem can be quantified.
- retrieve operational limits (from grid contingency registry) -> operational limit policy manager - evaluate forecasted measurements, calculated state-variables to the defined operational limits - validate grid quality (perform a state-estimation) - calculate and fill in missing states on equipments/measurements - retrieve action controls from OCR to adjust the predicted capacity on parts of the grid

The goal of this process is to provide various reports about operations. An example of such a report is a compliancy report, i.e., a report to justify that in a certain time frame Alliander complied with its contractually agreed on behavior. Similarly, reports to justify that a client did/did not comply with its contractually agreed on behavior. Financial reporting is a subprocess. Based on control actions, what were the financial consequences? Were they within the pre-agreed budgetary agreements for a given congestion area? Besides compliancy and financial reporting as stated above, the process also administers the operating limits and policies. Think of dynamic operating limits. As a consequence of dynamic limits the operating constraints per (client) contract may have to be re-evaluated.
The proces 'Operational Management & Reporting' provides reports on the financial and operational performance business indicators. It register the fincancial impact on remedial actions on the different products. The operational limits sets on equipments are provided and used to determine the risk for a grid configuration.

The 'Execute & Verify Solution Fulfillment' provides the analysis of the defined capacity situation, where there is sufficiency or insufficiency amount of transport capacity available is. The process performs a mix&match of available capacity products, such as early curtailment, redispatch, late curtailment or flexibility, on the different time-lines, such as day-ahead, intra-day and realtime.
In executing the fulfillment each capacity product has its own sub-process to carry out to settlements, this includes selection, offering, confirm and activate a settlement. The settlement includes operating and financial constraints on which the market participant need to comply.
In executing the fulfillment of the situation on the grid is guareded by a capacity settlement dossier and contains the progress state of the different settlement options. These options are offered by the connected and selected agents.
When a settlement is activated, there is a verification of the market participants complies with the agreed constraints, such as operating and financial.
The process finished, when the solution fulfillment performs all actions to solve the defined capacity situation or/and the residual risk is accepted.
The service reports on operational and financial business indicators, such as: - financial statement on contingencies - amount of power managed - financial validation of TenneT - etc.

To determine the risk level and corresponding 'energy system state', like alert state or emergency state policies applied. The specified policies are related to the different equipments and other parts of the grid.

A safety assessment is a result of a performed risk assessment and represents the 'system state' of an analysed part of the grid.
This includes: - the topological island with related equipments, - the connectivity between these equipments, - the exceedense of the operational limits , - the identified contingency equipments (the one causing the transport limitations) - the allocated operating constrains exchanged with the market-participants
The 'system state' gives direction in the possibility of reaching a solution. Here, the action perspective plays a role and thus also determines the serverity level.

The operating contraint is exchange as a schedule with the Market Participant on a defined RegisteredIntertie. This operating constraint is then related to the EnergyConsumer as ControlAction to make this connectively available for grid-calculations.

The Real-Time Operation (RTO) business function includes the execution of the planned action in regard to changing the network operational state. In addition, it monitors the current state of the network to ensure that the power grid is operating in a secure and balanced state. Predefined and activated remedial action will be executed when the pre-condition is met.
That a system is secure and balanced state means that there is balance between supply and demand and that the system can handle pre-defined unanticipated loss of system equipment without violating operational requirements in regard to voltage, frequency, and operational stability limits.

The Network Operation (NO) package in the CIM IRM defines the business functions and business objects involved in monitoring and operating the power grid as a whole system or the entities responsible for part of the whole system.

It also includes obligated operation planning that handles the " look-ahead" function to ensure that the " near future" operation based on committed schedules is an operation in a secure and balanced state.
